history.content: On CalCentral, click "Options" above your class list and you should be able to swap sections. It should tell you whether you'd be placed on a waitlist.

children.subject: If you check on schedule.berkeley.edu and click on each section, it will tell you the number of seats open, waitlist info, etc.
It has the symbols, but I have no idea if it will actually let me switch sections without putting me at the end of the waitlist for the section.

history.content: It has not been completely made clear to us how this works.  It seems like if the section is full OR (even if there is space) there is anyone on the waitlist for that section, then when you try to do this you will be kicked out of the class and put on the waitlist (apparently at the first position on the lecture waitlist if there is nobody currently waitlisted for that discussion/lab).  While I agree with the student who answered above that it "should tell you whether you'd be placed on a waitlist",  we've had reports from students who were moved from enrolled to waitlisted and they didn't notice any warning at all that switching sections would lead to them being kicked out of the class.
